cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language modeling. Additionally, it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel self-attention mechanism. It could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with improving the performance of Transformer models. Furthermore, it could be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it proposes a new method for learning attention span. Lastly, it could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as self-attention mechanisms are commonly used in computer vision tasks.
